<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1631,2018]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[277,361,1631,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–85" captionStartId="15.[151,263,962,985]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,194,941]" captionTargetId="figure-441@15.[306,1281,193,941]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 78–85. Wings. 78, Empis angustipennis Bezzi, lectotype ♀; 79, E. chiragra Bezzi, lectotype ♂; 80, E. induta Bezzi, female holotype; 81, E. leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 82, E. liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 83, E. lucidilabris Bezzi, ♀ from Peru; 84, E. penniventris Bezzi, holotype ♀. 85, E. spinifera Bezzi, lectotype ♂. Length of each wing informed along the text." pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) light brown with bands at level of r–m and dm–cu crossveins and at apex, pterostigma light brown; base of costal vein with robust seta (not represented in figure); dm cell rather elongate. Vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1368,1376,1682,1696]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">1</subScript>
bare dorsally, slightly dilated towards apex. Halter dark brown with yellow base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1631,2018]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Abdomen black, subshiny, finely grey pruinescent visible at certain angles. Tergite 1 with longer setae on posterior margin; remaining tergites with short but distinct setae. Sternites same color as tergites.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1631,2018]" pageId="11" pageNumber="74">
