<figureCitation box="[864,1004,1814,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–59" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1441,1464]" captionTargetBox="[268,1321,521,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-413@11.[262,1325,517,1420]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 50–59. Empis lucidilabris Bezzi, ♀ from Peru (Chamchamayo). 50, head, lateral view; 51, antenna, lateral view; 52, frons, frontal view; 53; thorax, dorsal view; 54, left foreleg, posterior view; 55, left midleg, anterior view; 56, right hindleg, anterior view; 57, terminalia, lateral view; 58, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 59, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view (cercus omitted). Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 50, 54–56 = 1.0 mm; 51–53 = 0.5 mm; 57–59 = 0.2 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Figs. 57, 59</figureCitation>
); tergite 10 with basal sinus (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1422,1814,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–59" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1441,1464]" captionTargetBox="[268,1321,521,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-413@11.[262,1325,517,1420]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 50–59. Empis lucidilabris Bezzi, ♀ from Peru (Chamchamayo). 50, head, lateral view; 51, antenna, lateral view; 52, frons, frontal view; 53; thorax, dorsal view; 54, left foreleg, posterior view; 55, left midleg, anterior view; 56, right hindleg, anterior view; 57, terminalia, lateral view; 58, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 59, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view (cercus omitted). Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 50, 54–56 = 1.0 mm; 51–53 = 0.5 mm; 57–59 = 0.2 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
); genital fork narrow (
<figureCitation box="[383,465,1849,1873]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–59" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1441,1464]" captionTargetBox="[268,1321,521,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-413@11.[262,1325,517,1420]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 50–59. Empis lucidilabris Bezzi, ♀ from Peru (Chamchamayo). 50, head, lateral view; 51, antenna, lateral view; 52, frons, frontal view; 53; thorax, dorsal view; 54, left foreleg, posterior view; 55, left midleg, anterior view; 56, right hindleg, anterior view; 57, terminalia, lateral view; 58, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 59, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view (cercus omitted). Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 50, 54–56 = 1.0 mm; 51–53 = 0.5 mm; 57–59 = 0.2 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="74">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
